src.memory

Class MemorySlot

  • java.lang.Object
    • src.memory.MemorySlot
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class MemorySlot
extends Object
implements Cloneable

    The MemorySlot class represents a memory slot read from the Minput.data file.

    Each MemorySlot has a start, and end address, a startMarker and endMarker, and a list of processes. The start address is the beginning of this memory slot. The end address is the end of this memory slot. The startMarker gives the starting address of the last process added to this memory slot. The endMarker gives the ending address of the last process added to this memory slot. The list of processes contains a list of processes allocated to this memory slot.

    Author:
    Richard I. Zhunio
